other_tests.findings: The liver is echogenic with a slight coarsened echotexture. A 2.0 x 1.9 x 2.2 cm cyst is present within the right lobe. There is no intrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. A distended gallbladder is present, top normal in size, with multiple shadowing stones that are mobile. No wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid is seen. The CBD is dilated, measuring 8 mm. No ductal stones are seen; however, the distal most segment of the CBD is not visualized. There is no ascites.
